title: For Sale:  ⌲⌲→Selling⌲⌲→ RARE CBC GR-8 “Black Beauty” (Remington Nylon 66) Replica Clone
postcontent:
⌲⌲→This Rarely found CBC GR-8 “Black Beauty” Nylon 66 replica, semi-automatic .22 LR rifle is a replica /clone of the Remington Nylon 66 Apache Black and Black Diamond variations with subtle differences, white stock diamonds verses black diamonds, blue finish receiver cover and barrel verses Apache Black Nickel/chrome receiver cover and barrel. This “Black Beauty is a Must have for Remington Nylon 66 collectors/enthusiasts.

The CBC (Cia Brasileire Cartuchos, Brazilian Cartridge Company) founded in 1926 is today one of the largest ammunition manufacturers in the world, imported this model rifle through F.I.E (Firearms Import and Export Corporation) of Miami, Florida from the late 1980s to 1990. In the 1930s Remington Arms owned interest in CBC and with the help of Remington’s engineering and production personnel they manufactured Remington firearms for the Brazilian market. In 1981 the Brazilian government nationalized CBC doing away with Remington’s interest in CBC. This new nationalized company was left with the industrial tooling and knowledge that enabled them to make a copy/clone of the Remington Nylon 66. The CBC GR-8 “Black Beauty” was the result.

The Original CBC blue finish is Excellent with some light handling marks and scattered very light discoloration, freckling. The Plastic/Nylon Black stock is near Perfect with only a few Very, very light storage/handling marks. The Nylon stock checkering is still very sharp. The bolt face, feed ramp, chamber and magazine feed tube are Exceptionally clean. The bore is Very bright and the rifling is sharp, showing few signs of being fired. This “Black Beauty” has the Original fully adjustable rear sight, note the large windage adjustment knob found mostly on the earlier Remington Nylon models along with a “Shark Fin” front sight. These CBC “Black Beauty” rifles are Rarely Found in this High Condition. Chambered for .22 Long Rifle, Semi-automatic, with a 19 5/8” Ordinance steel barrel. These rifles have a Unique butt-stock, tube feed, magazine with a total capacity of 14 +1 .22 LR rounds. These Nylon 66 and the replica rifles are well known for their Performance, Accuracy and Flawless function. The Nylon 66 rifle is considered by many to be the Finest .22 caliber, semi-automatic rifle, Remington ever made. A Rarely found, CBC “GR-8 Black Beauty” Remington Nylon 66 replica Long Rifle, semi-automatic rifle that is a Must have for your collection of Nylon 66 rifles. The total production of the Brazilian CBC was only 200,000. This rifle's serial number is GR 50999 and is in 95+% condition.

Priced right at $235.

The DPMS Panther LR-308T "NIB" is the tactical carbine. Compared to the LR-308 and LR-308B, the 308T's  Hbar barrel and shorter overall length made this rifle a favorite amongst hunters and law-enforcement alike. The LR-308T has a button-rifled 16" 4140 Chromemoly heavy barrel with a 6 grooves and a 1 in 10" twist. Like all DPMS Panther rifles, the LR-308 is built around a reliable gas-operated rotating bolt and an 8620 steel bolt carrier. The upper and lower receivers are made of 7075-T6 aircraft aluminum. The upper receiver is extruded from 6066-T6 aluminum and features a snag-free design and a smooth-side look with no dust cover, no shell deflector and no forward assist as well as a Picatinny rail for easy scope-mounting. The lower receiver is milled from a solid billet of 6061-T6 with a integral trigger guard, a standard AR-15 trigger group, and an aluminum magazine release button. The stock is a standard A2 black Zytel Mil Spec with trap door assembly and the handguards are carbine-length, free-float tube. 20-round magazine. Lever safety.

title: For Sale/Trade:  Custom BCM Midlenth for sale
location: Prior Lake, Minneapolis / St. Paul, Minnesota
postcontent:
This rifle has never been fired. I am willing to trade for a DDM4a1. If you're interested in this rifle, text me at REDACTED. I will send photos immediately.

 BARREL STEEL
Utilizing independently certified 11595E Mil-Spec barrel steel, are more durable than typical commercial barrels and specced to perform under heavy use in high-threat environments in extreme temperature conditions.

BARREL TESTING AND INSPECTION
Every chrome lined BCM® barrel is subjected to the Mil-Spec HPT(High Pressure Test) and then MPI (Magnetic Particle Inspected) to detect any possible flaws in the barrels surface, guaranteeing a more durable weapon.

BARREL PROFILE
11595E.
Every BCM® barrel uses the same Independently Certified Mil-Spec 11595E Barrel Steel (CMV) used in the USGI M16 family of rifles. Built to perform in extreme environments, BCM® barrels are stronger and more durable than typical commercial barrels, thanks to high concentrations of carbon and/or vanadium in the alloy.

HPT AND MPI
BCM® barrels also undergo a M197 HPT (High-Pressure Test), commonly referred to as a proof load, rating each barrel for 70,000 psi. This hardening is followed by a MPI (Magnetic Particle Inspection) to detect any possible flaws in the barrels surface, with both circular and longitudinal magnetic fields per ASTME1444-01 in the current Military-Specification.

MID-LENGTH GAS SYSTEM
Mid-length systems deliver the same compact size of a carbine, with less overpressure and recoil for a smoother running platform with more agile weapon control. The mid-length system also allows for a longer hand guard and by extension, a longer iron sight radius for improved accuracy when engaging with iron sights.

CHROME BORE AND CHAMBER
A chrome lined bore and chamber is now a worldwide standard in the industry for a battle rifle. The chrome bore and chamber is harder than the barrel steel and on the USGI M16/M4 rifles will aid in chambering, extraction, and reliability. It increases velocity, and also resists against fouling and corrosion from extended use in the field. This gives the end user a longer barrel life with less required time in maintenance and cleaning.

Comes with steel magpul back up iron sights (MBUS PRO), 3 30 round aluminum GI magazines, and 2 30 round polymer SwampFox magazines.
